crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a surrogate loader used to register/unregister COM DLLs. It receives instructions from a parent process via command-line arguments (handles) and a shared memory region. It reads a DLL path from the shared memory, loads it with `LoadLibraryExA`, and executes either `DllRegisterServer` or `DllUnregisterServer` based on a flag. This mechanism is a known malware technique to execute arbitrary code or establish persistence by registering a malicious COM object, effectively acting as a custom, stealthier version of `regsvr32.exe`.
